\title{Translation is not a linear operator}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-08}
\import{ela}
\taxon{non-example}

\p{Let #{V} be a real vector space. Let #{u\in V} be a nonzero vector #{u\neq\vec{0}}. The function #{f\colon V\to V} defined by #{f(v)=u+v} is not a linear transformation.}

\p{To see this, we find #{f(v+w)=u+(v+w)} but #{f(v)+f(w)=(u+v)+(u+w)=2u+(v+w)}, and #{u\neq2u} unless #{u=\vec{0}}. So #{f} cannot possibly be a linear transformation.}